  "prompt": "What is the maximum number of tabs open in Google or Computer?",
  "response": "The maximum number of tabs that you can open in a web browser like Google Chrome, Firefox, or others does not have a strict limit set by the browser itself. Instead, it is mainly limited by the available system resources (such as RAM) and how the browser manages memory.\n\nIn practice, users have reported successfully opening thousands of tabs, but performance will degrade as you open more, leading to slowdowns or potential crashes. For a smoother experience, it's generally advisable to keep the number of open tabs to a manageable number, such as a few dozen. However, for specific tasks or organization, some users may utilize extensions or features like tab groups to keep their tabs more organized.",
